%N A229024 a(n) is the minimum distance to n! for the sum-of-digits of any factorial.
%C A229024 One could talk of signed integers here: 0, 0, 0, +3, -3, +9, +27, -18, 0, 0, +9, +9, depending on whether the minimum sum-of-digits finds itself above (plus) or below (minus) n!. The problem with so doing is that there might exist some n for which a nonzero minimum distance is both plus and minus.
%C A229024 Zeros indicate where there are solutions in A228311.
